BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:ENT Expert Up Close: Latest Advances in Rhinoplasty and Sinus Surg
 ery
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260811T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260811T200000
DTSTAMP:20260720T070528Z
UID:29f8eccbe53b35b6@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:OverviewThis session will explore advanced surgical techniques
  and decision-making strategies in rhinoplasty that address both aesthetic
  goals and functional nasal airflow\, while also examining the complexitie
 s of different types of sinusitis and the role of surgery as a definitive 
 treatment option within appropriate patient care pathways. The activity wi
 ll highlight how structural and preservation approaches can be tailored to
  optimize form and function\, including in complex and revision cases\, an
 d will emphasize evidence-based technique and thoughtful preoperative plan
 ning to improve surgical outcomes and patient satisfaction.\n\nRegistratio
 nRegistration for all practitioners - free\n\nTo register for this activit
 y\, please click HERE.\n\nCreditsAMA PRA Category 1 Credits™ (1.00 hours
 )\, Non-Physician Participation Credit (1.00 hours)\n\nTarget AudienceSpec
 ialties - Allergy\, Immunology\, and Rheumatology\, Otolaryngology (ENT)Pr
 ofessions - Non-Physician\, Physician ObjectivesAt the conclusion of this 
 activity\, learners should be able to:\n1. Describe structural and preserv
 ation techniques that support both function and aesthetics in rhinoplasty.
 \n2. Identify key preoperative factors that influence airway outcomes and 
 revision risk.\n3. Name different underlying factors that can lead to chro
 nic sinusitis\n4. Review why some surgeries fail and others resolve chroni
 c sinusitis symptoms\n\nAccreditationIn support of improving patient care\
 , Stanford Medicine is jointly accredited by the Accreditation Council for
  Continuing Medical Education (ACCME)\, the Accreditation Council for Phar
 macy Education (ACPE)\, and the American Nurses Credentialing Center (ANCC
 )\, to provide continuing education for the healthcare team. \n \nCredit D
 esignation \nAmerican Medical Association (AMA) \nStanford Medicine design
 ates this Live Activity for a maximum of 1.00 AMA PRA Category 1 CreditsTM
 .  Physicians should claim only the credit commensurate with the extent of
  their participation in the activity.\n\nEvent URL: https://events.stanfor
 d.edu/event/ent-expert-up-close-latest-advances-in-rhinoplasty-and-sinus-s
 urgery\n\nSource: stanford_virtual
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/ent-expert-up-close-latest-advances-
 in-rhinoplasty-and-sinus-surgery
BEGIN:VALARM
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Reminder: ENT Expert Up Close: Latest Advances in Rhinoplasty 
 and Sinus Surgery
TRIGGER:-PT1H
